Package: spLeakage
Title: Detect and Quantify Spatial Information Leakage in Predictive Modelling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Olatunji", "Johnson", email = "teejaystatistics@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Diagnostic tools for spatial information leakage in predictive
    modelling. Given spatial data and a train/test split (or an existing
    modelling workflow), spLeakage detects and quantifies how much a validation
    scheme leaks information through spatial autocorrelation, estimates the
    resulting optimism in reported accuracy, and recommends an appropriate
    validation strategy for the user's sampling design and prediction target.
    It audits rather than generates folds, interoperating with established
    spatial cross-validation packages.
